\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.1}{\ignorespaces High-level architecture. The browser communicates with the system through an Nginx reverse proxy, which routes HTTP traffic to the FastAPI backend and WebSocket traffic to the Hocuspocus collaboration server. The principal persistence paths are shown: the backend writes to PostgreSQL with pgvector, and the collaboration server caches room state in Redis. Secondary connections (the backend also uses Redis for session caching, and the collaboration server periodically snapshots Y.Doc state to PostgreSQL) are described in the text below.}}{25}{figure.caption.12}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:arch-overview}{{4.1}{25}{High-level architecture. The browser communicates with the system through an Nginx reverse proxy, which routes HTTP traffic to the FastAPI backend and WebSocket traffic to the Hocuspocus collaboration server. The principal persistence paths are shown: the backend writes to PostgreSQL with pgvector, and the collaboration server caches room state in Redis. Secondary connections (the backend also uses Redis for session caching, and the collaboration server periodically snapshots Y.Doc state to PostgreSQL) are described in the text below}{figure.caption.12}{}}
